ATK vs DMG vs CRIT on Honkai: Star Rail¶

TLDR

Taking into account all possible bonus sources (relics, light cone, traces, ally buffs etc), calculate the following 3 measurements:

$$ \large \begin{align*} \text{ATK Score} &= 9 \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} + \frac{\mathrm{ATK_{flat}}}{\mathrm{ATK_{base}}} \right) = \underbrace{9 \times \left( 1 + \frac{\text{ATK Blue Number}}{\text{ATK Black Number}} \right)}_{\text{When there are no external ATK buffs}} \\ \text{DMG Score} &= 10 \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) \\ \\ \text{CRIT Score} &= 6 \times \left( \frac{1}{\mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} + \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \right) \end{align*}$$

The optimal balance between ATK vs DMG vs CRIT is achieved when ATK Score = DMG Score = CRIT Score. When not equal, your lowest score indicates the attribute your relics are most starved for. Try to "migrate" relic stats from your highest score to your lowest score.

Note: In lower investment, there are stat constraints that affect the optimization solutions (see KarushKuhnTucker conditions). In this case, ignore the CRIT Score and just use ATK Score = DMG Score while keeping $\mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}}$ and $\mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}$ to the smallest possible value.

Mathematical Proof

Damage formula:

$$ \large \begin{align*} \mathrm{DMG_{out}} = \left[ \mathrm{ATK_{base}} \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) + \mathrm{ATK_{flat}} \right] \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \times \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \right) \end{align*} $$
  • A main stat (or 10 sub-stats) is worth either:
    • 43.20% of $\mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}}$
    • 38.88% of $\mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}}$
    • 32.40% of $\mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}}$
    • 64.80% of $\mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}$
$$ \large \begin{align*} \mathrm{Cost} = \frac{\mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}}}{43.20\%} + \frac{\mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}}}{38.88\%} + \frac{\mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}}}{32.40\%} + \frac{\mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}}{64.80\%} \end{align*}$$

Lagrange multiplier:

$$ \nabla \mathrm{DMG_{out}} = \lambda \times \nabla \mathrm{Cost} \implies \Large \begin{cases} \frac{\partial \mathrm{DMG_{out}}}{\partial \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}}} = \lambda \frac{\partial \mathrm{Cost}}{\partial \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}}} \\ \\ \frac{\partial \mathrm{DMG_{out}}}{\partial \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}}} = \lambda \frac{\partial \mathrm{Cost}}{\partial \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}}} \\ \\ \frac{\partial \mathrm{DMG_{out}}}{\partial \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} = \lambda \frac{\partial \mathrm{Cost}}{\partial \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} \\ \\ \frac{\partial \mathrm{DMG_{out}}}{\partial \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} = \lambda \frac{\partial \mathrm{Cost}}{\partial \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} \end{cases} \implies \begin{cases} \mathrm{ATK_{base}} \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \times \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \right) = \frac{\lambda}{43.20\%} && (1) \\ \\ \left[ \mathrm{ATK_{base}} \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) + \mathrm{ATK_{flat}} \right] \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \times \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \right) = \frac{\lambda}{38.88\%} && (2) \\ \\ \left[ \mathrm{ATK_{base}} \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) + \mathrm{ATK_{flat}} \right] \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) \times \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}} = \frac{\lambda}{32.40\%} && (3) \\ \\ \left[ \mathrm{ATK_{base}} \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) + \mathrm{ATK_{flat}} \right] \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) \times \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} = \frac{\lambda}{64.80\%} && (4) \end{cases} $$

(3) divided by (4):

$$ \large \begin{align*} \frac{\mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}}{\mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} = \frac{64.80\%}{32.40\%} = 2 \quad\implies\quad \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}} = 2 \times \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \end{align*}$$

(2) divided by (4):

$$ \large \begin{align*} \frac{1 + \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \times \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}}{\left( 1 + \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) \times \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} = \frac{64.80\%}{38.88\%} = \frac{10}{6} \quad\implies\quad 6 \times \left( \frac{1}{\mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} + \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \right) = 10 \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) \end{align*}$$

(1) divided by (4):

$$ \large \begin{align*} \frac{\mathrm{ATK_{base}} \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \times \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \right)} {\left[ \mathrm{ATK_{base}} \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) + \mathrm{ATK_{flat}} \right] \times \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} = \frac{64.80\%}{43.20\%} = \frac{9}{6} \quad\implies\quad 6 \times \left( \frac{1}{\mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} + \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \right) = 9 \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} + \frac{\mathrm{ATK_{flat}}}{\mathrm{ATK_{base}}} \right) \end{align*}$$

(2) divided by (3):

$$ \large \begin{align*} \frac{1 + \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \times \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}}{\left( 1 + \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) \times \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} = \frac{32.40\%}{38.88\%} = \frac{10}{12} \quad\implies\quad 12 \times \left( \frac{1}{\mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} + \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \right) = 10 \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) \end{align*}$$

(1) divided by (3):

$$ \large \begin{align*} \frac{\mathrm{ATK_{base}} \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \times \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \right)} {\left[ \mathrm{ATK_{base}} \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) + \mathrm{ATK_{flat}} \right] \times \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} = \frac{32.40\%}{43.20\%} = \frac{9}{12} \quad\implies\quad 12 \times \left( \frac{1}{\mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} + \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \right) = 9 \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} + \frac{\mathrm{ATK_{flat}}}{\mathrm{ATK_{base}}} \right) \end{align*}$$

(1) divided by (2):

$$ \large \begin{align*} \frac{\mathrm{ATK_{base}} \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right)}{\mathrm{ATK_{base}} \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) + \mathrm{ATK_{flat}}} = \frac{38.88\%}{43.20\%} = \frac{9}{10} \quad\implies\quad 10 \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right) = 9 \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} + \frac{\mathrm{ATK_{flat}}}{\mathrm{ATK_{base}}} \right) \end{align*}$$

Therefore, the optimal balance between ATK vs DMG vs CRIT is given by:

$$ \large \begin{align*} \underbrace{9 \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} + \frac{\mathrm{ATK_{flat}}}{\mathrm{ATK_{base}}} \right)}_{\text{ATK Score}} = \underbrace{10 \times \left( 1 + \mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \right)}_{\text{DMG Score}} = \underbrace{6 \times \left( \frac{1}{\mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}}} + \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \right)}_{\text{CRIT Score}} \end{align*}$$

import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot, cm

base_ATK = 1200
flat_ATK = 360

curves = []

curve = {'label': r'$\mathrm{Optimal\; ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \;,\quad \mathrm{Optimal\; DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \;,\quad \mathrm{Optimal\; Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \;,\quad \mathrm{Optimal\; DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}$'}
curve['crit_Rate'] = np.linspace(0.25, 1.0, 1000)
curve['crit_DMG'] = 2 * curve['crit_Rate']
curve['score'] = 6 * (curve['crit_DMG'] + 1/curve['crit_Rate'])
curves.append(curve)

curve = {'label': r'$\mathrm{Optimal\; ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \;,\quad \mathrm{Optimal\; DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \;,\quad \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} = 5\% \;,\quad \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}} = 50\%$'}
curve['crit_Rate'] = np.full(1000, 0.05)
curve['crit_DMG'] = np.full(1000, 0.5)
curve['score'] = np.linspace(1.0, 50.0, 1000)
curves.append(curve)

curve = {'label': r'$\mathrm{Optimal\; ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \;,\quad \mathrm{Optimal\; DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \;,\quad \mathrm{Optimal\; Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} \;,\quad \mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}} = 50\%$'}
curve['crit_Rate'] = np.linspace(0.05, 1.0, 1000)
curve['crit_DMG'] = np.full(1000, 0.5)
curve['score'] = 12 * (curve['crit_Rate'] + 1/curve['crit_DMG'])
curves.append(curve)

curve = {'label': r'$\mathrm{Optimal\; ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \;,\quad \mathrm{Optimal\; DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}} \;,\quad \mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}} = 100\% \;,\quad \mathrm{Optimal\; DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}$'}
curve['crit_Rate'] = np.full(1000, 1.0)
curve['crit_DMG'] = np.linspace(0.5, 3.0, 1000)
curve['score'] = 6 * (curve['crit_DMG'] + 1/curve['crit_Rate'])
curves.append(curve)

for curve in curves:
    curve['bonus_ATK'] = curve['score']/9 - 1 - flat_ATK/base_ATK
    curve['bonus_DMG'] = curve['score']/10 - 1
    curve['out_DMG'] = (base_ATK * (1 + curve['bonus_ATK']) + flat_ATK) * (1 + curve['bonus_DMG']) * (1 + curve['crit_Rate'] * curve['crit_DMG'])
    curve['cost'] = curve['bonus_ATK']/0.4320 + curve['bonus_DMG']/0.3888 + curve['crit_Rate']/0.3240 + curve['crit_DMG']/0.6480



def plot(ax, curves, x, xlim, y, ylim):
    label_LaTeX = {'out_DMG': r'$\mathrm{DMG_{out}}$', 'cost': r'$\mathrm{Cost}$',
                   'bonus_ATK': r'$\mathrm{ATK_{bonus}^{_{\%}}}$', 'bonus_DMG': r'$\mathrm{DMG_{bonus}^{_{\%}}}$',
                   'crit_Rate': r'$\mathrm{Rate_{crit}^{_{\%}}}$', 'crit_DMG': r'$\mathrm{DMG_{crit}^{_{\%}}}$'}

    ax.set_xlabel(label_LaTeX[x], fontsize=14)
    ax.set_ylabel(label_LaTeX[y], fontsize=14)

    ax.set_xlim(xlim)
    ax.set_ylim(ylim)

    for curve in curves:
        ax.plot(curve[x], curve[y], label=curve['label'])

    ax.grid()
    ax.legend(loc='upper left')

fig, axs = pyplot.subplots(1, 2, constrained_layout=True, figsize=(24, 12))
plot(axs[0], curves, 'cost', [6.0, 11.0], 'out_DMG', [5000.0, 14000.0])
plot(axs[1], curves, 'cost', [6.7, 8.1], 'out_DMG', [6200.0, 8720.0])
axs[0].plot([6.7, 6.7, 8.1, 8.1, 6.7], [6200.0, 8720.0, 8720.0, 6200.0, 6200.0], 'k--')

fig, axs = pyplot.subplots(2, 2, constrained_layout=True, figsize=(24, 24))
plot(axs[0, 0], curves, 'cost', [6.0, 11.0], 'bonus_ATK', [0, 2.0])
plot(axs[0, 1], curves, 'cost', [6.0, 11.0], 'bonus_DMG', [0, 2.0])
plot(axs[1, 0], curves, 'cost', [6.0, 11.0], 'crit_Rate', [0, 1.5])
plot(axs[1, 1], curves, 'cost', [6.0, 11.0], 'crit_DMG', [0, 3.0])
